7. Your Rights Under UK GDPR

You have the following rights regarding your personal data:

- Right of access: Request a copy of the personal data I hold about you.
- Right to rectification: Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data.
- Right to erasure: Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be
  forgotten"), subject to legal obligations.
- Right to restrict processing: Ask me to limit how I use your data.
- Right to data portability: Receive your data in a structured, commonly used
  format.
- Right to object: Object to processing based on legitimate interests.
- Right to withdraw consent: Where processing is based on consent, withdraw it
  at any time without affecting prior processing.

